    {
      "id": 5334,
      "category": "researcher",
      "content": "*Thanks to the 18F team for the great experience, fast fix, and the bounty!*\n\nThis case was weird. The XSS worked only with few `&` chars in certain places (identified by trial-and-error method), and input appeared to be correctly sanitized without it.\nIt bypassed Chrome XSS auditor, and due to stripping chars function in place (hi `FILTER_SANITIZE_STRING`) it also bypassed Kona WAF using stripped chars in the payload. It is a curious example, how two different defense mechanisms neutralize each other.\nThe discovered XSS issue was site-wide and affected 80+ endpoints.",
